The paper deals with the problem of maximizing a monotone submodular function subject to a cardinality constraint in a streaming setting, which is a classic problem in the field of data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithm proposed in the paper is based on a novel partitioning structure and thresholding rule, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the performance of the algorithm in two different data summarization tasks, which falls under the category of data mining (cs.DM).
